    <p>Never Rarely Some­times Al­ways (2020, NC16)</p>
    <p>In this abor­tion drama, a girl named Au­tumn learns she is preg­nant and turns to the only per­son she trusts: her best friend and cousin Sky­lar. The teenagers travel from their con­ser­va­tive state to the more abor­tion-friendly New York in search of anonymity and a res­o­lu­tion.</p>
    <p>Re­drum, The Pro­jec­tor,</p>
    <p>Level 5 Golden Mile Tower, 6001 Beach Road Ni­coll High­way</p>
    <p>To­day, 8.10pm, & to­mor­row, 5.40pm $13.50, con­ces­sions avail­able</p>
    <p>the­p­ro­jec­tor.sg/films-an­de­vents/never-rarely-some­time­sal­ways</p>
    <p>Song Lang (2018, NC16)</p>
    <p>In this Viet­namese film set in 1980s Saigon, debt col­lec­tor Dung de­mands pay­ment from a Cai Luong folk opera com­pany. Linh Phung, a male star, is drawn to him. Their paths con­tinue to cross, melt­ing away mis­con­cep­tions as gang­ster and singer dis­cover they are kin­dred spir­its.</p>
    <p>Green Room, The Pro­jec­tor, Level 5 Golden Mile Tower, 6001 Beach Road Ni­coll High­way Var­i­ous dates</p>
    <p>$13.50, con­ces­sions avail­able the­p­ro­jec­tor.sg/ films-and-events/song-lang</p>


